  "SubGoals": [],
  "Description": "The TestMultipleAsks goal is designed to utilize caching to track the number of times a handler is invoked within a 10-minute window. It initiates a multi-question interaction on the 'user' channel by calling the MultiAskHandler. The goal asks three questions sequentially and stores the responses in variables. It then validates each response against expected values, throwing an error if any response does not match. If all responses are correct, it confirms the successful execution of multiple asks.",
